# Klingon Diplomatic Greeting Drafting

<div id="m-30000001-1701-4d00-8000-000000030001" data-msg-index="0" class="msg msg--anthropic">

## Human

*2369-04-14T10:00:00.000000+00:00*

<a id="b-30000001-1701-4d00-8000-000000030001-0"></a>Look up the Klingon greeting "nuqneH" and propose a respectful opening line for a diplomatic dispatch to Chancellor K'mpec.

</div>

<div id="m-30000002-1701-4d00-8000-000000030002" data-msg-index="1" class="msg msg--anthropic">

## Assistant

*2369-04-14T10:01:00.000000+00:00*

<a id="b-30000002-1701-4d00-8000-000000030002-0"></a><details><summary>Thinking</summary>

> "nuqneH" literally means "what do you want" — it's blunt by Federation standards but standard among Klingons. I should fetch a phrasebook to confirm register before recommending an opening.

</details>

<a id="b-30000002-1701-4d00-8000-000000030002-1"></a><a id="tu-toolu_FAKE0001ngfedcba9876543210"></a><details><summary>Tool use: web_fetch — Fetching: Klingon language reference</summary>

```json
{
  "url": "https://memory-alpha.test/wiki/Klingon_language"
}
```
</details>

<a id="b-30000002-1701-4d00-8000-000000030002-2"></a><a id="tr-toolu_FAKE0001ngfedcba9876543210"></a><details><summary>Tool result: web_fetch</summary>

```json
{
  "is_missing": false,
  "metadata": {
    "site_domain": "memory-alpha.test"
  },
  "text": "nuqneH (lit. \"what do you want\") is the standard Klingon greeting. In formal diplomatic contexts it is paired with the honorific \"qaleghneS\" (\"I am honored to see you\").",
  "title": "Klingon language — Memory Alpha (test mirror)",
  "type": "knowledge",
  "url": "https://memory-alpha.test/wiki/Klingon_language"
}
```

</details>

<a id="b-30000002-1701-4d00-8000-000000030002-3"></a>For a dispatch to Chancellor K'mpec, open with "qaleghneS, Chancellor — nuqneH?" ("I am honored to see you — what do you want?"). The honorific softens the bluntness of nuqneH; together they read as warm-but-direct, which Klingons respect.

</div>

<div id="m-30000003-1701-4d00-8000-000000030003" data-msg-index="2" class="msg msg--anthropic">

## Human

*2369-04-14T10:02:00.000000+00:00*

<a id="b-30000003-1701-4d00-8000-000000030003-0"></a>Perfect. Make it so.

</div>

